summary: This is an FBI 302 form documenting a proffer interview conducted on August 26, 2019, at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York. The interview was part of an investigation, with multiple law enforcement and prosecutorial officials present. The document itself is a summary of the interview, containing the agent's notes but no conclusions.

keyFacts: A proffer interview was conducted on August 26, 2019, as part of an investigation related to the Epstein case.
The interview took place at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the Southern District of New York.
Multiple officials were present, including Assistant U.S. Attorneys, an FBI Special Agent, an NYPD Detective, and an Office of Inspector General Special Agent.
The document is an FBI 302 form, which is a summary of an interview containing the agent's notes but no recommendations or conclusions.
The identities of the specific individuals (the interviewee and the officials) are redacted in this document.
